                  <summary>Verso contains 6 lines belonging to a letter and 1 line in the upper margin which contains the address of the letter on recto. The adressee's name of the letter on verso is Abu Ibrahim. The sender makes several requests ('God willing').</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Verso (parallel to fibres) contains 7 lines with the original cutting lines preserved on all four sides.</note>
                     <note type="general">Recto contains another letter. See nyu.apis.5530.</note>
                     <note type="local_note">Held in the Special Collections Department of Bobst library of NYU and stored loose in acid-free file folders.</note>
